main event: Two objects moving very fast from southeast to northwest were observed in Cincinnati, Ohio on December 18, 1960.
interesting points: The objects were described as yellow lights with an optical length of 2-3 feet., The sighting lasted for about 2 minutes., The observation occurred toward the setting sun, which ruled out a jet aircraft., The sightings were reported in an old document related to Project Blue Book., The report includes a request for additional information from witnesses to evaluate the sightings.
sighted object: two yellow lights in the sky
witness description: witnesses described the lights as moving very fast
